sed on your overall data model, I think SMS_TEMPLATE is a very good idea. Right now you're storing the TEMPLATE_ID in both SMS_RESPONSE and SMS_OPT_OUT, but the actual template text is repeated only in documentation. Having a master table makes the design much cleaner.
The overall flow I understand is:
SMS_OPT_IN_RAW
        │
        ▼
SMS_OPT_IN
        │
        │ (Apply suppressions)
        │   - SMS Opt Out
        │   - Other business suppressions
        ▼
Campaign Member List
        │
        │ Uses
        ▼
SMS_TEMPLATE
        │
        ▼
SMS Manager API
        │
        ▼
SMS_RESPONSE
        │
        └── Members replying STOP
                │
                ▼
           SMS_OPT_OUT
This makes SMS_TEMPLATE the master reference table for every campaign template.
