Table Description
I would make it consistent with your other tables.
The WellMed Central Quality Reporting team maintains the SMS_TEMPLATE table to store the approved SMS campaign message templates used for UHC membership outreach. Each record represents a business-approved SMS message associated with a campaign month and Template ID. The table serves as the master reference for SMS content sent to eligible members and is used by campaign generation processes as well as reporting of outbound SMS communications.
Column Descriptions
SMS_TEMPLATE_ID
System-generated unique identifier for each SMS Template record populated using a Snowflake Sequence.
TEMPLATE_ID
Business-defined identifier representing the approved SMS message template used for campaign communications. This value is referenced by SMS_RESPONSE and SMS_OPT_OUT.
PROGRAM_ID
Business-defined identifier representing the SMS program under which the template is used.
PROGRAM_NAME
Name of the SMS campaign program associated with the template.
CAMPAIGN_MONTH
Calendar month and year for which this SMS template is intended to be used.
CAMPAIGN_NAME
Business-friendly name describing the purpose of the campaign.
Examples:
Get Care
Bladder Health
Annual Care
Fall Prevention
Flu Shot
Mental Health
First Appointment
TEMPLATE_TITLE
Short descriptive title of the SMS template for reporting and administrative purposes.
SMS_MESSAGE
Complete SMS message content approved by the business team and delivered to eligible members during the campaign.
LANDING_PAGE_URL
Hyperlink embedded within the SMS message directing members to campaign-specific educational resources or healthcare information.
STOP_HELP_TEXT
Standard SMS compliance statement informing members how to opt out or request help.
Example
Reply STOP to stop; HELP to help.
EFFECTIVE_START_DATE
Date on which the SMS template becomes available for campaign use.
EFFECTIVE_END_DATE
Date after which the SMS template should no longer be used.
ACTIVE_IND
Indicates whether the template is currently active (Y = Active, N = Inactive).
