One suggestion to simplify the schema
Since every TEMPLATE_ID uniquely identifies a specific SMS message, you could avoid storing redundant text by making SMS_TEMPLATE the authoritative source for message content. Then:
SMS_RESPONSE stores only TEMPLATE_ID (already present).
SMS_OPT_OUT stores only TEMPLATE_ID (already present).
Reports join to SMS_TEMPLATE to retrieve the campaign name, message text, URL, and campaign month.
This keeps the SMS content in a single place and avoids duplication if message wording or metadata ever needs to be corrected. It's a clean dimensional design where SMS_TEMPLATE functions as a lookup/master table for all SMS campaigns
